711136f-a.text:
119-125 West 12th Street, north side, west of Sixth Ave., showing the First Reformed Presbyterian Church. In 1907, this structure became known as the Second United Presbyterian Church which was demolished in 1918. Upon this site was erected a 6-story apartment building which stands today (1938).

About 1910.

709356f-a.text:
Sixth Avenue, north from West 12th Street, showing demolition of the old 'E1" line. At the left are low buildings that extend across 13th to 14th Streets. On the right is the 10-story utilitarian structure occupying the 13th to 14th Street frontage and which was formerly the business establishment of R. H. Macy, department store retailer.
To the left is the towering Empire State Building.
February 119, 1939
P. L. Sperr
